    <h1>ricardo.ch</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>With plentymarkets, you have full access to ricardo.ch, the biggest online market in Switzerland. Learn how to list your items, retrieve orders and edit your listings. Invoicing and shipping is also carried out directly via your plentymarkets system.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Registering with ricardo.ch</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First register with <strong><a href="https://www.ricardo.ch/registration/schritt1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ricardo.ch</a></strong>. After you have finished registration, use the access data to set up your ricardo.ch account in plentymarkets. Please note that the ricardo.ch website is currently only available in German and French.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Setting up ricardo.ch in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In this chapter, you will learn how to create, edit and delete accounts as well as how to update your token. Furthermore, it is described how to create offer templates and text templates and how to set up event procedures for ricardo.ch.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">2.1. Activating accounts</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong> to activate new accounts for ricardo.ch. You need to have your access data consisting of the user name and password. Proceed as follows to add one or more accounts.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating a new account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add account</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Unlock or change account</strong> will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the <strong>Account</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to unlock your account.<br>
→ You will be forwarded to ricardo.ch and will have to authenticate your data.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the access data (nickname and password) of your ricardo.ch account and click on <strong>Authorize</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Close the window.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Synchronise account data now (token)</strong><br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The account will be displayed in the <strong>Accounts</strong> menu.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When ricardo.ch is successfully connected to your plentymarkets system, the following automatic processes are available:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Hourly order import</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Hourly data exchange</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A token can be renewed no earlier than 24 hours before the the regular duration ends.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Updating the token:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Update token</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Unlock or change account</strong> will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to update your token.<br>
→ You will be forwarded to ricardo.ch and will have to authenticate your data.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the access data (nickname and password) of your ricardo.ch account and click on <strong>Authorize</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Close the window.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Synchronise account data now (token)</strong><br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>→ The account will be displayed in the <strong>Accounts</strong> menu.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Top up your credit balance</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can top up your ricardo.ch credit balance directly on ricardo.ch. You need to have credit in order to <strong><a href="/en/omni-channel/multi-channel/ricardo-ch#360">start</a></strong> listings.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong> to rename or delete accounts.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Renaming an account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the account you want to rename.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a new name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Rename account</strong>.<br>
→ The account will be renamed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting an account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete account</strong>.<br>
→ The account will be deleted.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Reload</strong> to update the account list.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="400">2.2. Updating options</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The setting <strong>Update options</strong> in the <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Accounts</strong> menu allows you to update your listing settings and to fix problems, e.g. if no payment method of a ricardo.ch listing has been selected.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Original currency and standard currency are different</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Additional information is saved for orders that are imported with a different currency than the standard currency saved in plentymarkets. In this case, both the original currency and the original gross and net amounts will be saved for every item included in the order.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="500">2.3. Synchronising offer templates</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The setting <strong>Synchronise offer templates</strong> allows you to synchronise your ricardo.ch <a href="http://www.ricardo.ch/verkauferportal/de-ch/ratgeber/beitr%C3%A4genachverkaufsphasen/einstellen/angebotsvorlageninmyricardo.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>offer templates</strong></a> with plentymarkets. The offer templates will then be available for your ricardo.ch listings in the <strong>Listings » Edit listings</strong> menu. You will find them in the <strong>Market</strong> tab in the <strong>Link to template</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="600">2.4. Saving text templates for ricardo.ch</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>System » Markets » ricardo » Settings</strong> to save texts for <strong>Terms of guarantee</strong>, <strong>Payment conditions</strong> and <strong>Delivery conditions</strong> as well as texts for <strong>Automatic feedback</strong>. You can enter German and French text templates in the text fields. Expand <strong>Other</strong> to set which item name is to be used in the listing title or listing subtitle for the second language.</p>
</div>
